<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.822/73: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-24T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            24, 1919, noon.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your 173, November 19, 11 a.m.</p>
                            <p>Department approves your interpretation of instructions contained in
                                Department’s October 16, 2 p.m., and believes that no further
                                message in connection with Roncador Cay should now be sent. Please
                                inform Department at once if Colombian Government re-initiates the
                                matter.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>